This commit removes commands that are not supported because the community version of SONiC does not allow the mgmt-framework container to read data from JSON files.

Unit Test (before fix):
```
sonic# show system
%Error: Application Failure
sonic# show system cpu
%Error: Application Failure
sonic# show system memory
%Error: Application Failure
sonic# show platform
%Error: Information not available or Not supported
sonic# show platform syseeprom
%Error: Information not available or Not supported
```

Unit-test (After-fix):
```
sonic# show system
  processes  Show system processes information

sonic# show
  interface  Show Interface info
  ip         show IP commands
  lldp       Show lldp information
  system     Show system information
                                                         <<------ no more platform command.
sonic# show
```

We could update procdockerstatsd to get the required info.

1) Include 'lstart' to 'ps -eo ...' command to get the complete timestamp of start, which can be converted to epoch
2) 'ps afu' can be used to get memory usage to the granularity of KB. Memory allocation unit being pages (often 4K), you may just multiply by 1024 to get bytes

3) It does record %CPU. If you need some additional refinements, we could do.

The error message could be seen here:

http://central.maven.org/maven2/io/swagger/swagger-codegen-cli/2.4.5/swagger-codegen-cli-2.4.5.jar

```
501 HTTPS Required. 
Use https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/
More information at https://links.sonatype.com/central/501-https-required
```

According to the 501 error response data, http://central.maven.org/maven2 should be changed to https://repo1.maven.org/maven2. Therefore, the Makefile change in this PR should be:

`https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/io/swagger/swagger-codegen-cli/$(CODEGEN_VER)/$(@F)`

For reference, please see this [post](https://support.sonatype.com/hc/en-us/articles/360041287334).
